{
  "text": "The cell adhesion assay was performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, each well of a 96-well ELISA plate (Costar, Cambridge, MA) was coated with laminin-332 and then blocked with 1% BSA. Cells (2 6 10 4 cells) were added to each well in supplement-free keratinocyte growth medium and incubated for 20 min. After non-adherent cells were removed by vigorous shaking, adherent cells were fixed with 25% (w/v) glutaraldehyde for 10 min and stained with 0.5% crystal violet (w/v) in 20% (v/v) methanol for 10 min. The dye was extracted using 0.1 M sodium citrate in 50% methanol (v/v) for 30 min. Then, absorbance at 590 nm was measured using a microplate reader.",
  "correct_citation": {
